# Spidometr SDD

Before editing firmware, read root `AGENTS.md` and the task `handoffs/*/handoff.md`.

- Canonical / working source: `sketch_jul19a/sketch_jul19a.ino`
- Owner flashes and tests this sketch on real hardware
- One task at a time: finish and hardware-test before starting the next
- Do not tackle the whole project or pack multiple features into one change
- Spec first: update `AGENTS.md` if contract/pins/EEPROM/UI change, then write `handoffs/<slug>/handoff.md`, then code
- Do not change pins or EEPROM map without updating `AGENTS.md` first
- One handoff = one goal; no drive-by refactors
- No `delay()` in `loop()` unless the handoff explicitly allows a splash in `setup`
- Prefer minimal diffs; do not sync `src/main.cpp` unless the handoff says so
- Briefly comment new/changed code lines; do not duplicate nearby identical comments
